Get Ratio Matrix of Phosphoproteome Data

getRatioMatrix.Rd

getRatioMatrix calculates the ratio matrix of phosphoproteome data from a MultiAssayExperiment object.

Usage

getRatioMatrix(maeData, normalization = FALSE, getAdjustedPP = FALSE)

Arguments

maeData

A MultiAssayExperiment object containing phosphoproteome and full proteome data.

normalization

A logical value indicating whether to perform normalization. Default is FALSE.

getAdjustedPP

A logical value indicating whether to use adjusted phosphoproteome data. Default is FALSE.

Value

A numeric matrix representing the ratio of intensity of PP (phosphoproteome) data to FP (full proteome) data.

Examples

# Load multiAssayExperiment object
data("dia_example")
# Call the function
getRatioMatrix(dia_example, normalization = TRUE)
